data.title: RuPaul’s Drag Race Reveals First-Ever Global All Stars Cast: Alyssa Edwards and More Competing on Paramount+
data.meta_description: Meet the 12 queens competing in the first season of RuPaul’s Drag Race Global All Stars, premiering Aug. 16 on Paramount+.
data.text:
Practice those tongue pops, America, because Alyssa Edwards is officially representing the good ol’ U-S of A in the first-ever edition of RuPaul’s Drag Race Global All Stars, which revealed its full cast on Monday.

The iconic queen, best known for her unforgettable turns on Drag Race Season 5 and All Stars 2, will face off against 11 queens, each from one of the reality competition’s many international iterations, when the Paramount+ series premieres on Friday, Aug. 16 with back-to-back episodes. Along with a $200,000 grand prize, the fan favorites will also compete for the title of “Queen of the Mothertucking World.”

Additional competitors from around the world include:

* Athena Sorgelikis (Drag Race Belgique Season 1)

* Eva Le Queen (Drag Race Philippines Season 1)

* Gala Varo (Drag Race Mexico Season 1)

* Kitty Scott-Claus (Drag Race UK Season 3)

* Kween Kong (Drag Race Down Under Season 2)

* Miranda Lebrão (Drag Race Brazil Season 1)

* Nehellenia (Drag Race Italia Season 2)

* Pythia (Drag Race Canada Season 2)

* Soa de Muse (Drag Race France Season 1)

* Tessa Testicle (Drag Race Germany Season 1)

* Vanity Vain (Drag Race Sweden Season 1)

RuPaul will host the competition, joined by regular judges Michelle Visage and Jamal Sims. A rotating group of celebrity guest judges will be Ru-vealed at a later date.
